                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d514">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.51632 National City Bank/22: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-04-01T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 1, 1930—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. National City Bank reports that no progress has been made toward a decision
                    in the matter of the fine of its São Paulo branch. Bank feels that an informal
                    inquiry on your part would help to expedite matters and the Department would be
                    glad to have you make such inquiry unless you perceive some objection thereto.
                    Please report by cable the cause of the delay, action taken by you and result
                    thereof.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
